t break frequencies at similar\nluminosities and no obvious global relation (but such a relation cannot be\nruled out for individual sources). We speculate that different magnetic field\nstrengths and/or different radii of the acceleration zone in the inner regions\nof the jet are likely to be responsible for the observed scatter between\nsources. (abridged)\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 7 Nov 2012 20:02:36 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-12"}
